## Code Quality

### Biome
- All code must pass `biome check` before committing
- No unused imports or variables
- No `console.log` in production code; use proper logging

### Functions
- Max 50 lines per function; extract if longer
- Prefer pure functions where possible
- Async functions must handle errors explicitly

### Imports
- No default exports except Next.js `page.tsx` / `layout.tsx`
- Group imports: external libs → internal modules → types
- Use path aliases (`@/`) consistently

### Forbidden Patterns
\`\`\`ts
// ❌ Never use `any`
const data: any = ...

// ❌ No implicit returns in async without error handling
async function fetchData() {
  const res = await fetch(url) // missing try/catch
  return res.json()
}

// ✅ Correct
async function fetchData() {
  try {
    const res = await fetch(url)
    return await res.json()
  } catch (error) {
    throw new Error(`Failed to fetch: ${error}`)
  }
}
\`\`\`